From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NIXOS_PORTS <local@nixos-ports>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/sunxi: skip commit_init_connecting() when no display
 is connected at boot

sunxi_drm_bind() unconditionally calls commit_init_connecting() after
setup_bootloader_connecting_state() returns >= 0. But that function
(via init_connecting()) returns 0 even when no bootloader connecting
info exists AND no connector currently reports a connected mode -- in
that case it just starts a hot-plug poll timer
(sunxi_drm_create_mode_monitor) and leaves pri->priv->connecting_head
EMPTY.

commit_init_connecting() then calls sunxi_drm_offline_mode_pre_init()
and sunxi_fbdev_init(), both of which correctly bail out on the empty
list with "init connecting not found" errors -- but execution then
falls through into drm_atomic_commit() with an untouched/empty atomic
state, which hangs the boot indefinitely on this BSP when no display
(no HDMI, no eDP/DP-altmode) is attached, as on this headless Cubie
A7S server build.

Skip commit_init_connecting() entirely when connecting_head is empty,
matching the same early-exit already used for the ret < 0 case just
above. Has no effect when a display IS connected/detected at boot
(connecting_head will be non-empty and commit_init_connecting() still
runs as before).
---
 bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c b/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
@@ -1274,6 +1274,10 @@
 		DRM_ERROR("setup bootloader connecting failed.Skip commit_init_connecting.\n");
 		goto dev_register;
 	}
+	if (list_empty(&private->priv->connecting_head)) {
+		DRM_INFO("sunxi-drm: no display connected at boot, skip commit_init_connecting\n");
+		goto dev_register;
+	}
 	commit_init_connecting(drm);

 dev_register:
--
2.43.0
